CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, pg. 22, reads: "Beauty - Rieck's Dairy Company booth which was assembled by Dan Savle, sales promotion man, was made even more attractive by Mrs. Eunice Brown, who gave away hundreds of quarts of Sealtest Buttermilk to the sampling audiences."
TitMainTitle: Eunice Brown, pouring Sealtest milk samples, standing at Rieck's Dairy Company booth, at the 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair, Ammon Recreation Building, Hill District
